\section{Conclusions}\label{conclusions_ch3}

In this chapter the basic formulation of FDTD using Yee algorithm has been discussed. Absorbing boundary condition (ABC) has been used for absorption of outgoing waves. Unsplit Step PML formulations are discussed. Details of Gaussian pulse used for excitation are detailed. FDTD is a time domain method - also been the method of obtaining frequency domain result from time domain data using Fourier transform has also been discussed here. Near-field to far-field transformation is discussed for computation of far-field radiation pattern. Simulation of perfectly plane wave in FDTD grid, which is the essential parts for analysis of an antenna in receiving mode, is discussed here. The H-plane and E-plane patterns of pyramidal horn antennas have been computed. The predicted results show good agreement with available measurement. Also, diagonal plane radiation radiation pattern of pyramidal horn antennas have been computed. Finally, the usage of FDTD in the analysis of an antenna in receiving mode for EM field sensor application and the usage for RCS prediction is also discussed in this chapter.
